title: SHWF to attend food safety and health meetings in Beijing, Kunming and Ottawa
content_text:
p>The Secretary for Health, Welfare and Food, Dr York Chow, will visit Beijing, 
Kunming, Yunnan and Ottawa, Canada from Wednesday (October 19) to October 27 for 
meetings on food safety and health. He will leave for Beijing on Wednesday for the signing of a Co-operation 
Arrangement with the State General Administration for Quality Supervision, 
Inspection and Quarantine on October 20 to further enhance the cooperation of

Inspection and Quarantine on October 20 to further enhance the cooperation of 
food safety, inspection and quarantine between the Mainland and Hong Kong. Joining Dr Chow in the Beijing trip are the Director and Deputy Director of Food 
and Environmental Hygiene, Mr Gregory Leung and Dr Mak Sin-ping. Dr Chow will then depart for Kunming, Yunnan on October 20 to lead the Hong Kong 
delegation to attend the Fourth Joint Meeting of Senior Health Officials of the 
Mainland, Hong Kong and Macao to be held on Friday and Saturday (October 21 and

22). Members of the Hong Kong delegation include the Director of Health, Dr Lam Ping-yan; 
Director of Food and Environmental Hygiene, Mr Gregory Leung; Controller of 
Centre for Health Protection, Dr Leung Pak-yin; Chief Executive of Hospital 
Authority (HA), Dr Vivian Wong; Deputy Director of Food and Environmental 
Hygiene, Dr Mak Sin-ping; Director (Professional Services and Operations) of HA, 
Dr Cheung Wai-lun; and Deputy Secretaries for Health, Welfare and Food, Ms Susie
Ho and Mrs Ingrid Yeung. Dr Chow will return from Kunming to Hong Kong on October 22.
